manifestation.dialog: 'ey runt, going off to your gramps' 'ouse?
... <Colligan grunts in dismay>
Aye, 'e asked you a question mate! *pushes Colligan*
<Colligan lands on big kids shoe, with a thud>
Youve fallen and sullied my attire, runt! Whats wrong with you? Gonna to make me challenge the day after I take me rites?
You cant challenge one who isnt of age, or hasnt your father taught you that?
My father taught me to fight! What of it, its practice, right boys <motions to other children>?
To fight, get within melee range of your opponent and swing weapon around so as to inflict bonus damage by the extra force. Sometimes, however, it isn't worth it...
<grunts> I give you win! <gurgle, cough spit> thats the finest beat down youve ever given
Maybe I need to best meself then, I need practice fleeing too right?
<suddenly scared, realizing this is a serious situation. He could die, looks down searching ground> Your father didnt <sputter> teach you to flee, though?
<confused> What are... ye blatherin...
Colligan suddenly pulls a wrench from nearby, and catches the Bully offguard...
Argh! Not fair, officer aid me!
<comes in tentatively>
When in combat with multiple melee enemies, remember to keep moving and keep moving your weapon. Swinging your weapon more means more blocking and damage bonuses.
No, good job Col, you must have learned well from your grandpa <kids walk away, leaving two in extreme pain>
<pained groan> You alright, boys?
I think you broke my wrist! Im gonna get you soon, boy! Git back, wonder why no one likes you!
Colligan walks slowly off again
Yeah, your friends count...
Anyone else want practice?
Catching up to the smoke, Colligan sees his brother crashes in the middle of the town proper. There are many people in the market, each face recognizing the other.
Col, its time to get up, head off to...
<interrupting excitedly> Wooo of course! Ive been up all night, it is time to go now. I cant miss the first-trans ledge flight - I just have some finalizing steps on the pack.
Ha... be sure to get something to eat before heading out
Hey runt, where are you running off?
I'm going to Gramps, finalizing the tests for...
<interrupts> ...more tinkering? You've got to quit going out there soon, we on the council deem him unsafe, then he may not be so free to do what he wants.
The council wishes to bring its "justice"? C'mon father, he's harmless, were just testing a useless gadget. Like it's so different from healing research in appendage reconstruction?

Your mom tells me how useless it is... Putting on functional replacements are one thing, but extending the human body to incorporate new abilities? Just keep it between your brother and you, then? Can't let the town get word of what you are doing today.
<grunts, salutes> Yes, sir
<tentatively> When are we...
<interrupts forcefully> He's not ready, not even of age yet. We've got to be careful with this one, they're... <trails off, looks away frustratedly, leaves.>
Whoa my boy, good to see you! You look worse off than normal!
<grunts> I dont know why I come. Why do we do this gramps?

You know Col, you are special, and have a desire to understand and provide things that benefit these people? They are just too blind, belligerent, and bafoony to realize the common good. You are my grandson, you know. Come, let me care for you.
It's just...
<interrupts>: Just not worth it? Of course not! These foolhardy folks so passionately seek to bring you down, the standards are so...
...stop! You mustn't say that! You know it is against standards; it will put us in danger. Dad has been warning me, I'm sure you too.

Will it put us in more danger than what we are working on? Their pontifications on our own ponderous plots is too gross; but moreso they fear our inklings to pursue our passions. It is itself an affront to them more than our plots. It is freedom they disagree with, as change is a chancy virgin best left untouched.
You are the most confusing conspiracist I know
One can only hope. I am rubbing off on you indeed, in grammar if not in thought, am I not? Though you and I both know your heart.
I understand neither your grammar nor your heart.
Of course, but you are a splendidly brilliant chap of fifteen. You get that from your father *wink.* Come, lets explore the problem before us.
Col, well met! Ready to... whoa are you okay?
Im fine, lets finish
The young one has been challenged
But he is not of age? Who did this? Havent they respect for standards? Let me challenge!
Challenge what? You challenge standards, fight the council? Heh heh... let us take our own challenge, the sky remains untouched by us! It is certainly not going to challenge itself.
You are confusing, gramps
Colligan motions at Cohiggan in triumph, indicating he is right in being the most confusing person around
Im old and confused as well, dont worry. Foolish challenges...<sad pause> Let us see what this mess was. Col, did you inspect the issue we were having with the cantankerous crank?
The factory fashioned a new one, along with the pins. And yes, we updated the boilerplate firewall yesterday, he should be fine.
Should is young....
<cutting off gramps> yeah, we've checked it a dozen times! It worked similarly for all trials before this!
Well theres just a few concepts Im still parsing... *pauses briefly, then ruffles* well.. just a quick trip then
But we were going to shoot for the ledge across the way! Didnt you say you learned to communicate with them, they are waiting for us today!
They understand these setbacks, patience wins the day! Take it easy, and if you are okay, then off you go!
<excitedly> woo time to get off this rock... the first person to fly to another ledge! And brother can next!
When you touch down, fasten quickly and leave the pack running for when I cross over behind you to save me some time!
Col, we'll need to modify it special to accommodate your augmentations, boy, but your time will come eventually. Now, did we forget anything yesterday?
Of course not, its set gramps!
Fine fine, ready to say farewell, friend? You have packed your...
<interrupts> of course I'm tooled up and have food and supplies. I'm ready now <moves to launchpad>

<aside, to Colligan>: his patience he gets from his father, or lack thereof: remember my boy, life is not such a race, savor your victories as much as the process to get there. Your life isnt the sum of accomplishments.
Then you write your book on process while we bask in victory, thats a good trade off.
Touche, it is time I suppose.
C'mon gramps, this is the culmination of many years! Lets go celebrate victorious and wish Coh well!
All right, mr mini mechanic, go ahead and push to the boiler. Kick the crank and...
Will do, this really is nothing new gramps.
But a new scope, brother! A new ledge, I can see it now... are they waving? The first conversation? I wonder if they speak the same language! The first of many hopefully.
Col, you attached the safety rope?
You mean the civilization bridge? Of course, I want to communicate with them more than Coh. I dont see him getting in any challenges. Farewell!
Whoa whoa... let's just... did we prepare... is it ready?
Cohiggan and Colligan together exclaim: "Yes!"
<chuckles> if young men deferred to older wed never accomplish anything, I suppose
<serious, puts hand on Ratchets shoulder>: Gramps its your life dream, are you ready?
Of course my body, your manic mechanic has set you up for a splendid ride! Tell the pretty women across the way Ratchet says hi!
<flippantly> Sure gramps, farewell!
Off ye go...
The gauges read the boiler is engorged, let this bird fly!
Cohiggan grabs giant lever, ready to pull back, looks at gramps. Ratchet nods slowly, giving a slight grin.
As Colligan sweeps the lever in one big motion, the primary claw holding Cohiggan is released, and he is propelled into the air.
Cohiggan travels a bit toward the opposite ledge, but suddenly there is a backfire and black smoke comes pouring out.
Bah! Lad, grab the rope and tell him hes got to come back, that black billowing wont let us see whats happening.
Colligan tugs the rope three times, signaling Cohiggan to retreat back to the garage to wrench on the jetpack further.
Bah, thats not good response, come back my boy!
I can't.. see... <turns crank to pull in rope quickly> him!
Careful lad, need to give him slack to land again...<looks at guage> oh, no..!
Whats...
A crank pin broke, the flywheel must be erratic and completely out of control, come get the blower theres no use for us now, hes got to reel himself...
Get down! He's going to crash... oh no, he gave it full...
<exasperated> The boiler is at critical load, hes going over the warehouse... why?
He doesnt want to risk blowing us or the gear, blasted idiot! Quick, garage topside!
Must leave the rope, my boy, he'll just drag you with him, quick follow him! Bring him back if you can! Take the path over the warehouse to the elevator and down the chute!

Colligan arrives back at gramps, winded and a little beat up. He enters the open door to gramps, doesnt find him, and goes to the warehouse, where Gramps is furiously preparing a foreign object in about the shape of the last jet pack.
To pull a switch, walk up to it and press the action button (by default 'e')
To crouch, hold crouch key (by default 'left control' or 'c'). This will allow your torso to rotate, which can aid you in combat in certain scenarios by going prone or squeezing through tight areas.
You will die a lot in ledge. Upon death, press the action key or F2 to respawn at the last save. Saves within levels are frequent, so be aggressive!
When nearing an elevator or similar object, jump inside and press the action button (by default 'e' or 'enter') to activate
<Gasp>
Thats col and coh... what have they...
Theyve continued the..!
Have they no respect for standards!
Where's the councilmen?
<running up to Cohiggan, gasping>: Coh get up we need..
<twisted up in metal, legs burned, arms burned, bloodied, and sooty>: Col, we won the best kind of challenge...
Erm... <gasping as he sees the breadth of damage to his brothers body> let me try to... get...
No, you must leave, go back, flee
What'd I do...
You did nothing, we dreamed of change and it has been wrought, now go before the council comes and shows what they believe is the manifestation of change!
<screaming>: No..! I must stay!!!
Whatd you do to...my boy?
We didnt... the tests...
You...<eyes turn to Coh> you certainly broke the norm. <looks at Col, steeling himself> Colligan, you need to run to Ratchet immediately. Tell him what happened, tell him to go ahead. Go now.
But, brother I... Father I dont understand, Cohiggan... <holds his brothers hand>
Looking around quickly, Carragan stands up, pushes his son, and screams
Go! Do what I said!
<looks in disbelief>: I'm sorry, I did... I'm sorry Coh... <cry>
A kid from group earlier bumps into him, looks disapprovingly, shoves him away, and he starts running back.
A councilman steps out and tries to seize Colligan, but he hits him hard. Councilmen turns and yells how fierce the boys are, and the rest of the men on the way engage Col on the way back to gramps.
As Colligan enters the workspace, he sees Ratchet furiously tinkering with a multitude of objects Colligan has never seen before.
Gramps, Coh didn't... Coh didn't have...
Ratchet pauses activity briefly, still looking at his tools. After a short pause, he resumes.
Gramps, what do I do?
Ratchet pauses again briefly
What... father was there, he said to come to you, tell you brother was messed up, and that we should go ahead.
Colligan appears like he is winding up to shout, Ratchet looks up with his head curiously cocked, sufficiently such that Colligan is given pause.
Your father has his brief moments of clarity, yes, it is time for you to take the next point of challenge.
What do you mean? You challenge me?
Heh of course my boy, every day we challenge... come, witness this.
This is a small device, I'm unfamiliar with it, I dont...?
My boy, the device your brother flew was not an original.
Is, what..?
This is the original. That was but a copy.
No. It is too small, and theres no boiler?
This is a combustion augmented with solar elements, Col. This operates differently: it is lighter and more safe.
Why didn't we...?
This is clearly foreign, we couldnt trade a steam engine for a combustion and fly! We were likely to get punished just for using the copy, now this device.
Ratchet motions to the device, and a slight wave of understanding passes Colligan's face, followed by a further furrowing of the brow.
What's this...
Col, you are to take this pack and fly to the other ledge.
What! That's not... father wouldnt approve.
Your father said you need to take this pack and go. We've crossed the line, we are...
Father what? He knows about... whered you get this?
From above of course, weve been keeping it.
A commotion stirs outside, as a nearing onslaught of bitter folks stream nearer. Ratchet perks his ears at them, with some knowledge of their plans.
It is time now.
Ratchet primes, then pulls a cord hard twice. A motor revs to life.
Ah, its so loud.
Combustion for now while solar cells charge, the price of living I'm afraid. You are to take off now. Go to the other ledge, they will keep you.
But, brother... father...
It is too late. you must go. It is their wish to see one person evade the punishment of standards..

Colligan obstinately steps back and crosses his arms, resisting the degree of change he is presented. He motions helplessly toward the space beyond Ratchets airpad, from which he will launch, and from which no native has ventured. His protestations are answered by the clamoring of disgruntled villagers streaming in.
Rob-bot, come immediately and assist takeoff.
What is this, Rob-bot...?
A curious and foreign entity suddenly lights up and stands up. Humanoid in appearance, Colligan is awestruck by similarities in motor function and intelligence.
Greetings mortal, time to go.
Rob-bot swiftly whisks the pack to the launchpad.
He's a foreigner, quite a challenge *wink.* It is time. He is abreast of the situation - be well, may we meet again!
You can't stay, I am not leaving..!
The flesh is weak. The time is now.
Bind acknowledged
The humanoid suit again impresses Colligan by attaching to the jetpack, and by extension Colligan.
This does not ... oh this fits perfectly... did you...?
Hey there is that deviant, you broke my stand!

Colligan now faces the mob of angry people, ready to execute their justice on him. The way is clear to the West, and he is ready to use this new technology and fly away from this ledge, his home, family, possibly forever.
Rob, launch!
Rob-bot increases the throttle on the jetpack, met with a roar from the exhaust and a significant power edge on the steam jetpack Cohiggan used, propelling Colligan vertically much faster.
You..! They are escaping! Get the blunderbuss!
While hovering high above his home, Colligan, in a daze, sees men raise flared muzzles at his direction. As lead pellets screamed by, it took all he had not to pass out.
As a round penetrates a cylinder on the combustion jet pack behind him, he too is engulfed in black smoke.
Haha, Rob and you shall be close, now go Rob-bot, and Col: be free, just not right now! Ha, ha!
Filling the sky, the engine sputters as Colligan's threshold for consciousness is surpassed.
Colligan arrives in shock to the sewers. Through here he must reach and activate the mill, which he may scale to get to Ratchet's relatively hidden.
Colligan may stumble upon some inviting objects. To try to operate things, jump on or near them and press the action key (e by default).
Looks like I need to get that mill moving to scale the hill...
Greetings young traveler, my name is Vasht. Can you understand me?
Well met.
Colligan musters a rote response, still in a daze awakening in a different land. He turns his head, with a whimper of a cough.
Salaam, I see you have brought far wonders. You have arrived in my homeland, we have treated your wounds and talked to your shiny friend.
Ahh, thank you... I have shiny...
Colligan snaps up in the bed, suddenly lucid.
Rob-bot?
Mmm yes, he intimated as much, he is outside meditating in the presence of the sun.
Colligan breathes a sigh of relief seeing a familiar object, Rob-bot, opened to the sky charging through his solar cells.
He is curiously at peace, how about you, traveler? What is your destination?
I am... exploring. My name is Colligan. Thanks for treating me.
It is our pleasure, stay as you wish, young traveler. May you reach your destination, salaam. It is time to nourish your body, a day is a long time without sustenance.
Vasht motions to a nearby table containing a beverage, with an aroma similar to tea. Colligan picks it up and sips slowly out of the calming drink.
I have been unconscious a day?

You came to us dreaming, traveler. After a loud noise we found you outside and brought you in. This morning, we found your partner basking in the glory of the outdoors. He looked in poor shape. We tried to tend to him, but he has a unique skin.
Ahh, well, he is a robot, he.. accepts... a different kind of care. Thank you for this refreshment, is there time to see him before supper?
There is always time, do as you wish, salaam.
Thanks! Out this way...
Colligan steps out of the front door to desert, sees rob-bot opened up just outside house, and approaches him.
Rob-bot, oh my, are your systems operational?
Greetings, mortal.
Are you... functional?
Colligan steps back and cocks his head to the side, giving the robot a mechanics once over of the integral parts.
My systems are functioning, despite your best efforts. Energy levels back up to optimum levels.
Thats good... they have fuel here in the desert?
*syntax error, correcting* Affirmative, my solar receptors have gathered optimum levels of energy.
Solar... huh. Well, good. What happened, where are we?

*grammar match: stack* You have directed us south-west from our last departure point. We are running on a ledge beneath. *pop* We have flown from your ledge to the desert ledge. I took over autopilot as you passed out, a lead pellet fractured and shorted an energy cell. After recovering the pellet, I have brought the energy cell back to 51% efficiency. Other components suboptimal. Seek repair.
Noted, I can look at that later today. We are on a ledge... beneath..?
Affirmative.
Can you elaborate?
With destination unset it was inferred after recovery that your intention was to land here.
That... works... How can we get back up?
Uknown.
Anything else you feel like elaborating on...
A roar that has been steadily getting louder suddenly passes the threshold of ignoring, as a huge flying metal object is flung across the sky. Colligan looks in amazement.
That was a mark 18-c air to surface gunship
They must be quite advanced here, confusing given their home. Where have you seen their science facilities?
Unknown
How do you know of the... gunship?

West air force research and development was funded in part by the national science group with aid by the defense ministry in 1905. The first mark 18 was in production in 1908, followed by iteration b in 1910 and c in 1912.
Where is... ah, I think I need energy first Rob-bot. Lets go inside and share with...

Again interrupted, Colligan first looks on the flying vessel with annoyance. As balls of metal and fire fall toward Vashts home and explodes in a glorious sea of fire and hail of brick and mortar, his petulant look turns to horror. He gasps in confusion.
How did that...
The mark 18-c has GERW air to surface missiles, capable of...
The gunship destroyed Vasht..?
*grammar match: stack* Affirmative. *pop* missiles, capable of a range of 6000 meters...
As Rob-bot voice trails off in Colligans brain, rattling off a variety of fun mark 18 facts, Colligans mindset is transitioned back to that of flight.
Its time to head out, come with me
Affirmative, bind process initiated
Bah, what are you doing?
The bind process was designed to facilitate and strengthen suit users to bring faculties not normally available to mortals.
Huh, well, time to test out, farewell Vasht, thanks for...
As another explosion resounds, Colligans resolve is formed. The way West is the only path open.
Colligan runs West to next house and sees group of three soldiers, one in the house shouting
Get on your knees and stay calm, I cant let you stay up in an aggressive position!
This is our house, and I must stand in the presence of the woman, you have no respect for sacred rites?
Sir, you must sit down or we will use force!
My wife is right here, we mean no aggression but we musnt acquiesce...
As the scene unfolds before Colligan, he is overcome with hatred and again thinks to bring justice for the helpless family.

Colligan eyes the corpse of the soldier wielding the gun. Half disgusted, and half intrigued, he slowly creeps up to it. As he grips it, Rob-bot beeps in understanding, and Colligan decides on this being another tool through which he may administer justice to this uncalled for attack on a peaceful people group.

Interesting, I underestimated these folks hints of peace. Unfortunate to upset the natural balance, but we need to bring swift action to the interloper. Bring E1/E2 here to fortify the entrance to the facility, they mustnt pass here. Make other e squads systematically go over the terrain and...
With a downcast aspect, the officer responds.
Affirmative sir, I understand, Ill call them in now.
Interloper, there! Give up!
Argh... why would they take out Vasht and such a peaceful area? They didnt seem to like it but acted anyway, not too unfamiliar I suppose. What is this forest beneath us, another ledge?
Rob-bot, thoughts? Huh. Suppose I should see this facility and if it can help me get home... or somewhere...
E3 hasnt reported in, despite P2 and P3 reporting success in the initial run. Other teams report little resistance.

Passing through the bunker, Colligan finds interesting housing. Looking beyond in awe, he sees a vast canopy of trees below him. It appears another ledge is close enough to build a gondola down to this forest area.
Upon killing the guard in the tower, Colligan snatches up the much more fancy looking weapon. It appears to shoot multiple times, and Colligan wonders at the effectiveness with which they can kill.
Weve found few signs, sir. He definitely came down this way, but the rain has washed the trail.

Affirmative, call to base to warn them. He is dangerous, request backup as well to ensure he doesnt get near enough to learn anything. Command has issued shoot on sight, so prepare your weapons, soldiers.
Yes, sir!
Sir, interloper identified West!
Fire!
We got another!
We bring fresh body, elder
Good, more to bar... ah, he is too young to be of those we fight.
He looks different elder, we bring him to you to judge.
The elder again blesses the journey west to confront the greedy above-worlders. Cheers from the crowd resouds, as men gather sticks and blades for the potential brawl.
Charge!

Colligan enters the facility. It feels abandoned, then sees stairs down. As he heads down, there is a horrible smell. He finds a a shaft leading to a wealth of dead bodies, while an opposing shaft houses bodies not far from death.
Colligan opens the door and finds a garage in which he can fix parts on jet pack. There are many items with which he may tinker.
Better go check with Samel back in the clearing.
It is finished, weve defeated them and brought back your people. Those who are not before you never will be.
They are dead... we expected this. Let us purge this place <looks at soldiers>
Let them go. Those soldiers dont know what they were doing, they just followed orders.
They are bad, they took ours.
No, he took yours <points at security officer>. We need to end it, throw them in the desert.
The desert is suitable punishment... we can return to peace.
You are free to head back to the desert. Feel free to tell the your people of what happened, we dont mean harm, please let us be. If you come back, however, do not be surprised to share his fate.
Yes thank you, interloper.
Interloper? What is the meaning of that?
This is the name given to those performing the illegal action of traveling to or from an undoctrinated ledge.
Doctrination? What is this?
You must know with the technology to jump - you are indoctrinated since you have sufficient tech to cross leges, you cant hide this.
You look too young... this boy doesnt know what we are talking about. Boy, where did you get the gear to fly?
I made it.

What?? Assuming you arent lying, well, your society is near indoctrination then. Weve been monitoring your people for a long time. We thought he gave it to you... We wont report this, but dont be surprised when in the next few time cycles you get back to find a very different home.
You impose rules on those of different scientific levels? You standardize this and decide what people groups can do?
We cant let everyone have freedom, there is a danger.

What he means is, we wish to keep all ledge societies safe. Since we in the top three ledges have benefited so greatly, we wish to monitor others and keep people safe and well loved. It is for good, dont worry young one.
My people are agitated, time to go soldiers. <pause as they leave> You - Colligan - where are you going?
I must use the garage to fix my gear, hopefully there is sufficient material to get it, then I should leave.

You are to stay on the west side of the ledge then, marked by a trees length in the forest outside of the gate, it is yours... but if you happen to get lost, perhaps you may find food at my peoples table.
Ha thanks Samel... maybe I will see you again...
Bye, do well!
Thank you, brave one. You are good. Hope you find your people.
Thanks, may you make many more of your people.
<grins> Very well, bye
Colligan turns toward the garage, mind set to tweak Rob-bot and the devices therein.
<menacingly> Stop! I am Will, ascended to top 3! Fear my power! You are trespassing and harming innocent soldiers while rejecting our authority. Surrender now or meet a bloody justice!
There is nothing innocent about your soldiers! They came to take those dearest to the natives, what gives you the right to administer justice!
Further in the distance, a transport ship lands on top of an inner gate building. An officer with a grim smile comes up and passes Will, whose impassioned stance eases slightly.
Top3 Will, you are demanded back at Central. You are to leave immediately and let us resolve the situation.
My research is... taken care of. Why is...
Will hesitates a bit, then turns around and walks abruptly toward the ship
We will clean up, no worries. Leave us to clean the trash.
Will looks back in surprise, gasps abruptly, opens his mouth, but continues on determined
No! He cant just walk away from this mess, he should atone for the people that he has taken! How can you take living beings..!
I didn't...!
<bruskly interrupting Will> Leave him to me, sir! Orders are to get you back ASAP! I will finish this!

<looks back at Colligan> You see fool, he doesnt know what you are talking about. It was I who took these natives. It is easy to demonize those different from yourself, see each others disgust? I took the natives and incapacitated them so Will could continue his... research. A pleasant outcome is that both natives and soldiers are preoccupied.
What research? Theres not jet power here?
Jet power? Haha! There is just raw human power here!
You took the people! You... killed them, then used them for yourself? That man..Will? Harvested them for power? You are evil!
The transport ship takes off, carrying Will and supplies off to the distance
You won't live to see what power we've created! Now, prepare to meet my might!
<sputters> soon you will see his iron will... *points inside complex*

Across a wide open courtyard of old, broken stones are stairs leading to an ivy and moss covered structure. On top of the walls stands a man in a prideful stance, with a staff flickering electric blue.
He looks different, we bring him home.
We beat him now!
No! We go home safe.
Erghh... home safe. Go now to Samel, up in trees!
Doesn't look like the others, perhaps he isn't tradeable
OWW! Im not even of age yet to join them, I am fighting them!
Of age... desert people speak of age. It is important to them. It is not to us; those *motions West* take from us no matter what age we are. Of age is living to us.
We trade him for ours!
No, they kill us. Hes worth nothing, you should not have brought him.
We kill him?
What other options?
Kill! Kill they take our own!
No use otherwise, but...
A bit beyond, Small4 runs up breathing heavily
Many dead behind clearing! Everyone gone!
More gone..! Kill!
We can slow, think...
No think, Kill!
No not ours, theirs dead!
Theirs is dead? Where ours?
Ours is alive, theirs is dead.
Kill!
No bad, this one killed theirs! He has brought us closer to getting ours back! For now, we talk! You! Tell us why you are here.
Ah, I traveled from above... to explore... I am... impressed by your strength and wisdom. I was alone above...
Quiet! We know you are from the desert, why did you kill the soldiers?
I was running away, I didn't want to kill them. I just wanted peace again but they made me... I ran from then on. Where are we?
No questions. You are desert folk, then we need to bring you back there. Otherwise my people will try to avenge their losses.
I cannot go back, they have destroyed the desert ledge! I need to go on!
You obey the elder, bad!
I.. obey, I just suggest that you allow me to continue to....
Bad..! You..
Wait, you continue on... West? You do what you have been doing?
Yes, I am heading West.
Samel motions to group to huddle a little further away out of hearing range of Colligan, though still clearly audible.
He continues forward and kills west.
No he go free, bad!
Ahh no, he go free, good - he kill bad, we see our people!
If he goes West, either he gets caught or dead from soldiers or makes it West and lets us save our people!
Mmm... free good? Free see our people, yes! Good!
*looking conspiratorially* He better be...
I am good! Aside from eavesdropping... me good, and I will head West and go to the facility and help you free your people!
Hmm yes... but the facility is bad, many guards. We aid you in going... from behind.
That sounds better. I will help you get your people, and we can get to the facility to fix my stuff.
Agreed, we attack after food! Guard, cut his binds, now we eat, then we save our people!
A long and simple, yet satisfying meal nourishes those mustering the determination to march West.
You go scout out ahead, we follow. We help rush gate, then take back our home.

Colligan is lying in the garage near asleep after weeks of tweaking Rob-bot and a radio. He caught a curious signal a while back, and his been listening less and less intently to static as days go by. He is lonely, as the small, primitive folks have mostly abandoned him, and misses his home.
